text: George Olcott Proctor (February 23, 1847 – March 4, 1925) was an American politician who served in the Massachusetts House of Representatives and as the tenth Mayor, of Somerville, Massachusetts. ==Notes== Category:1847 births Category:Massachusetts city council members Category:People from Rockingham, Vermont Category:Massachusetts Republicans Category:Members of the Massachusetts House of Representatives Category:Mayors of Somerville, Massachusetts Category:1925 deaths
title: George O. Proctor
